Cynoglossum lanceolatum

originates from Yemen (
Kӧnig et al. 2015
) but reported from Africa (
Ge-Ling et al. 1995
), Pakistan, India (
Joshi 2016
), the Mediterranean, and throughout Asia (
Verdcourt 1991
) and Madagascar (
Kӧnig et al.2015
). In South Africa it occurs widely in all provinces, it also occurs in eSwatini and Lesotho (Figure 
14
). It is a widespread species that grows in disturbed habitats throughout parts of Africa.
